secureDisplaySummary: When turned on, the content on the screen is treated as secure, blocking background snapshots and preventing it from appearing in screenshots or from being viewed on non-secure displays.
dialogMessageWhatIsPassphrase: Passphrase is similar to password but generally longer, it will be used to encrypt and decrypt your notes. Use strong passphrase and make sure to remember it. backupSummary:
This will create an encrypted local backup, which gets automatically updated every day. Moreover, the backup is designed such that it can be used in tandem with other open-source tools like SyncThing to keep the multiple redundant backups across different devices on the local network.
To switch to a new device, you would simply need to copy this backup file to the new device and import that in your new Safe Notes app.
For more, see FAQ.
